  <prompt>
    Wire `GetStartedCardsWidget` (built in task 041) into the application: (a) register it
    in `ContextWidgetRegistry` so it can be resolved by widget type, (b) update
    `ContextPaneController.tsx` so the welcome stage renders `GetStartedCardsWidget` INSTEAD
    of `PlaybookGalleryWidget` (FR-21: PlaybookGalleryWidget remains REGISTERED for non-welcome
    stages â€” do NOT remove it from the registry), (c) wire each card's onClick to dispatch
    a `widget_load` event on the `workspace` PaneEventBus channel with the FR-19 widget-type
    mapping. The Assign Work card has special handling â€” it dispatches to a launcher built
    in task 045 (or you may pass through a special widget_type the launcher subscribes to).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React 19 + Fluent v9 frontend developer experienced with widget registries, PaneEventBus
    multi-subscriber wiring, and three-pane shell stage lifecycle. Comfortable with the
    `workspace` channel dispatch pattern from R2 lessons-learned.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three changes ship together:
    (1) `ContextWidgetRegistry.ts` registers `GetStartedCardsWidget` under the widget type
        `get-started-cards` (or equivalent canonical name). `PlaybookGalleryWidget` registration
        is RETAINED â€” both widgets remain resolvable by type.
    (2) `ContextPaneController.tsx` welcome-stage rendering swaps from PlaybookGalleryWidget to
        GetStartedCardsWidget. Non-welcome stages continue to resolve PlaybookGalleryWidget
        (or any other context widget via existing `context_update` events).
    (3) The `onCardClick` callback passed to `GetStartedCardsWidget` dispatches a `widget_load`
        event on the `workspace` PaneEventBus channel with the correct widget type per the
        FR-19 mapping table. Assign Work click is handled per task 045 (either dispatch a
        special widget_type that the AssignWorkWizardLauncher subscribes to, or invoke its
        function export directly â€” chosen consistent with task 045 design).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-18 places GetStartedCardsWidget on the welcome stage of the Context pane. FR-19
      maps each card to a Workspace-pane widget via the `workspace` PaneEventBus channel
      (the canonical multi-subscriber pattern from R2). FR-21 preserves backward
      compatibility: PlaybookGalleryWidget remains registered so non-welcome stages (or
      mid-session `context_update` events that switch to a playbook) still work. This task
      brings tasks 040 + 041 together and is the focal point where the welcome-state
      redesign goes live.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/registry/ContextWidgetRegistry.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/context/ContextPaneController.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">GetStartedCardsWidget consumed via its package export (`src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/...`). Do NOT inline its implementation. PlaybookGalleryWidget registration MUST be retained â€” its registry entry is required for non-welcome stage resolution per FR-21.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">No hex literals, no `rgba(...)` literals introduced in any code edited here. Any new styling uses `tokens.*`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No `accessToken` props or state. The widget_load dispatcher does NOT pass tokens via event payloads. Workspace pane subscribers fetch tokens themselves via `authenticatedFetch` / `useAuth()`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Welcome stage MUST render GetStartedCardsWidget. Non-welcome stages MUST continue to render PlaybookGalleryWidget (or whichever widget the stage lifecycle resolves to). Reusing the existing `workspace` PaneEventBus channel is REQUIRED â€” do NOT invent new channels (per project CLAUDE.md "do NOT invent new channels" rule).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">FR-19 mapping table (exact widget_type strings): Create Matter â†’ `create-matter-wizard`; Create Project â†’ `create-project-wizard`; Assign Work â†’ launcher invocation (per task 045 â€” coordinate exact mechanism); Summarize Files â†’ `document-upload-wizard`; Find Similar â†’ `find-similar-wizard`; Send Email â†’ `email-compose`; Schedule Meeting â†’ `meeting-schedule`. These strings MUST match exactly what `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry` and tasks 043, 044, 045 expect.</constraint>
  </constraints>

