  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read ContextWidgetRegistry + ContextPaneController">
      Open both files. In the registry, locate how `PlaybookGalleryWidget` is registered
      (registration pattern, key name, lazy-resolution approach). In the controller, locate
      the welcome-stage branch that currently renders PlaybookGalleryWidget. Map out the
      minimum surface area to edit.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Register GetStartedCardsWidget in ContextWidgetRegistry">
      Add a registration for GetStartedCardsWidget under widget type `get-started-cards`
      (or the canonical name aligned with task 041's export). Follow the existing
      lazy-import / factory pattern used by PlaybookGalleryWidget. Do NOT remove or modify
      the PlaybookGalleryWidget registration.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Swap welcome stage to GetStartedCardsWidget in ContextPaneController">
      In `ContextPaneController.tsx`, update the welcome-stage rendering path so it resolves
      `get-started-cards` instead of the previous PlaybookGalleryWidget reference. Preserve
      non-welcome stage logic (it should still resolve PlaybookGalleryWidget for stages /
      events that request it).
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Get PaneEventBus workspace-channel handle">
      Inside ContextPaneController (or via a small helper hook), obtain the `workspace`
      channel dispatcher from PaneEventBusContext. This is the existing canonical channel â€”
      do NOT create a new one.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Define onCardClick handler dispatching widget_load">
      Build an `onCardClick(widgetType: string)` function:
      <steps>
        <step>If widgetType === 'assign-work' OR equivalent special-cased value, invoke the
              AssignWorkWizardLauncher (task 045) â€” exact mechanism per task 045's contract
              (either a direct function call or a dedicated event type the launcher subscribes to).</step>
        <step>Otherwise, dispatch a `widget_load` event on the `workspace` channel with the
              widgetType in the event payload.</step>
      </steps>
      Pass this handler as `onCardClick` to `&lt;GetStartedCardsWidget /&gt;` on the welcome stage.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify mapping table â€” exact strings">
      Cross-check each card's widgetType against tasks 043 (`create-project-wizard`,
      `find-similar-wizard`), 044 (`email-compose`, `meeting-schedule`), 045 (Assign Work),
      and existing widgets (`create-matter-wizard`, `document-upload-wizard`). The strings
      MUST match exactly. If task 041 used different strings, harmonize here OR update task
      041 â€” but harmonize.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Smoke-test the wiring end-to-end">
      Build SpaarkeAi. In Vite dev or Power Apps host: load welcome state, confirm 7
      GetStarted cards render. Click "Create Matter" â€” confirm the existing
      `CreateMatterWizardWidget` opens as a new top-tab in the Workspace pane (active). Click
      "Summarize Files" â€” confirm `DocumentUploadWizardWidget` opens. Switch to a non-welcome
      stage (or trigger a `context_update` for `playbook-gallery`) â€” confirm PlaybookGallery
      still resolves.
    </step>
  </steps>

